title: Renaming listByParent method

question: In our service we have hierarchy like this DisconnectedOperation -> Image -> Artifact, for Image we already have name listByDisconnectedOperation but for Artifact it has listByParent instead of listByImage so is there any way to rename this for newer versions, I've tried like this
```
namespace Microsoft.Edge;
@doc("Disconnected operations artifact resource.")
@parentResource(Image)
model Artifact is ProxyResource<ArtifactProperties> {
    ...ResourceNameParameter<Artifact>;
}

@armResourceOperations
interface Artifacts {
    @removed(Microsoft.Edge.Versions.v2026_03_01)
    @doc("List by parent")
    listByParent is ArmResourceListByParent<Artifact>;

    @added(Microsoft.Edge.Versions.v2026_03_01)
    @doc("List by Image")
    listByImage is ArmResourceListByParent<Artifact>;

    @doc("Get the resource")
    get is ArmResourceRead<Artifact>;

    @doc("Get artifact download link.")
    listDownloadUri is ArmResourceActionSync<
        Artifact,
        void,
        ArmResponse<ArtifactDownloadResult> | ErrorResponse
    >;
}
```
but it didn't work, so is it okay to have this name or if not how we can change for newer versions?

